---
title: Querying the JSON RPC API
metaTitle: Querying the JSON RPC API
---

Mantis supports all [standard web3 JSON-RPC APIs](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API#json-rpc-methods).

## Enabling HTTP access

Use the following Dkey in order to enable the HTTP RPC API access:
```
-Dmantis.network.rpc.http=true
```

Once enabled, you can access the HTTP API through port 8545 over HTTP or websockets.

Example:

```
curl -X POST --data '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"net_peerCount","params":[],"id":1}' http://localhost:8545
```


## Geth console

You may use the Geth Javascript console in order to access the API as well.

1. Start Mantis with RPC enabled

```
./mantis-launcher etc -Dmantis.network.rpc.http=true
```

2. Run the Geth javasctipt console and attach to the endpoint

3. Call an API method on console

```
> net.peerCount
1
> â–ˆ
```
